[b]ICF Tournament Rules (2 or 4 players)[/b]

[b]Setup[/b]
• 9 white coins, 9 black coins, and 1 red Queen in the centre
• 2 players (1v1) or 4 players (2v2 — partners sit opposite)
• Team 1 pockets white, Team 2 pockets black
• The breaking player always plays white

[b]Taking a Shot[/b]
• Place the striker on your baseline
• Flick the striker to hit coins into the corner pockets
• You must shoot from your own baseline only

[b]Turns[/b]
• Pocket your own coin: you go again
• Pocket nothing: turn passes to the next player
• Pocket opponent's coin: they get credit, your turn ends
• Pocket the opponent's LAST coin: you LOSE the board — their colour is cleared, so they win by the number of your coins still on the board. Never finish your opponent's coins for them.

[b]The Queen[/b]
• You must pocket at least one of your own coins before claiming the Queen
• After pocketing the Queen, you must "cover" it by pocketing one of your own coins — same shot or the very next shot
• If you fail to cover: the Queen returns to the centre
• You cannot pocket your last coin before the Queen is covered — doing so loses the board
• Queen bonus: +3 points to the board winner — but NO Queen bonus if the winner is already at 22 or more points

[b]Fouls[/b]
• Striker pocketed: one of your own pocketed coins returns to the centre
• Striker leaves the board: same penalty as pocketing the striker
• If no coin is available to return, the penalty is owed and deducted from your next pocket
• Pocketing your last coin without the Queen covered: you lose the board
• Pocketing your opponent's last coin: you lose the board (they win by your remaining coins)
• A clean miss (no coin touched) is not a foul — your turn simply ends (per the ICF laws, there is no no-contact penalty)

[b]Scoring[/b]
• The team that pockets all their coins first wins the board
• Winner scores 1 point per opponent coin remaining on the board
• Queen bonus: +3 points if the winning team covered the Queen (no bonus if already at 22 or more points)
• Match is played to 25 points (first team to reach 25 wins)

[b]Player Configurations[/b]
• [b]1v1[/b] (2 players) — Two players, opposite sides. Each pockets their own colour.
• [b]2v2[/b] (4 players, Teams) — Two teams of two. Partners sit opposite. Teammates alternate turns and share a score.
